L,'opening-draftsmen-s-congress',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'15.12.2015\r\n',NULL),(320,0,'2016-04-27 16:12:24','2016-04-29 02:12:38',330,'NICOSIA AIRPORT ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'nicosia-airport',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Pawel Althamer \r\nRafal Zurek\r\nMichał Mioduszewski\r\nBrian Fernandes-Halloran\r\n',NULL),(321,1,'2016-04-28 10:50:24','2017-05-25 15:32:51',7,'UNDO',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'321',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nA critical journal in English and Greek',NULL),(322,1,'2016-04-28 15:17:54','2017-04-19 14:36:05',48,'MARIUS DYBWAD BRANDRUD ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'marius-dybwad-brandrud',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br/>\r\nBio\r\n\r\nMarius Dybwad Brandrud (b. 1976, Sweden) studied Photography at Gothenburg University. He received an MA in Fine Arts from Konstfack, in Stockholm, and an MA in Film Directing from the School of Film Directing, Gothenburg University.\r\n\r\nHis full-length feature [*After You*](https://vimeo.com/57528336) premiered in 2013. He was nominated for a Guldbagge Award for Best Cinematography for *Involuntary*, 2009, and in 2012 he was awarded for his work on*Play*.\r\n',NULL),(323,1,'2016-04-28 16:42:40','2017-06-01 23:36:17',191,'DOMUS 986',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'domus-986',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />December 2014',NULL),(324,0,'2016-04-28 16:49:04','2016-10-31 15:12:52',201,'KONSTANTINA ZANOU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'konstantina-zanou',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bio \r\n\r\nKonstantina Zanou (b. , ) living in New york, is a postdoctoral researcher at the Centre de Recherche en Histoire Européenne Comparé, Université Paris-Est Créteil. She received her Ph.D. from the Università di Pisa in 2007 and since then she has held research fellowships and teaching positions at the University of Nicosia, New York University, Centre for Advanced Studies Sofia Bulgaria, and Queen Mary University of London. \r\n\r\nShe is the co-editor (with Maurizio Isabella) of *Mediterranean Diasporas. Politics and Ideas in the Long Nineteenth Century* (Bloomsbury, forthcoming in July 2015) and the author of numerous articles on Greek expatriate intellectuals and national consciousness in the post-Venetian Adriatic, as well as on the spaces of the in-between in the Mediterranean. Her book in progress is tentatively titled *Stammering the Nation. Transnational Patriotism in the Mediterranean, 1800-1830*.\r\n',NULL),(325,1,'2016-04-28 17:27:46','2017-06-03 17:21:24',5,'LEFTERIS CHARALAMBOUS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'lefteris-charalambous',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nDr Lefteris Charalambous (b. 1974, Cyprus) holds a PhD from the Aristotle University of Thessaloniki. He is a conservator specialising in Cypriot mosaics and has been involved in various conservation and heritage management projects. He currently works for the Cyprus Department of Antiquities.\r\n\r\n(2015)',NULL),(326,0,'2016-04-28 18:38:09','2017-03-14 12:09:39',178,'DESPO PASIA',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'despo-pashia',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bio\r\n\r\nDespo Pasia (b. 1969, Cyprus) living in Nicosia, is a Museologist and Museum educator. She is currently a PhD candidate at UCL - Institute of Education, University of London. Her research concerns the educational use of museum photographic archives and centres on a phenomenological investigation of children’s encounters with photographic constructions of gender in urban Cyprus between the 1940’s and the 1960’s.\r\nShe has curated contemporary art exhibitions and has designed educational programmes for archaeological, historical and contemporary art museums in Cyprus and Greece, Erasmus+ and Marie Curie research programmes. Her research interests include photography, hybrid displays, museum studies and museum education.',NULL),(327,1,'2016-04-28 18:58:05','2017-06-07 22:20:43',252,'DEXTER SINISTER',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'dexter-sinister',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\n[Dexter Sinister](http://www.dextersinister.org/index.html?id=35) is the compound name of David Reinfurt and Stuart Bertolotti-Bailey. David graduated from University of North Carolina in 1993, Yale University in 1999, and went on to form O-R-G, a design studio in New York City. Stuart graduated from the University of Reading in 1994, the Werkplaats Typografie in 2000, and co-founded the arts journal *Dot Dot Dot* the same year. David currently teaches at Princeton University. Stuart currently teaches at the University of Geneva. \r\n\r\nIn 2006, Dexter Sinister established a workshop in the basement at 38 Ludlow Street, on the Lower East Side in New York City. The workshop intended to model a *Just-in-Time* economy of print production, running counter to the contemporary assembly-line realities of large-scale publishing. This involved avoiding waste by working on-demand, utilising local cheap machinery, considering alternate distribution strategies, and collapsing distinctions of editing, design, production and distribution into one efficient activity. \r\n\r\nIn 2011, together with Angie Keefer they set up *The Serving Library*, a not-for-profit cooperatively-built archive that assembles itself by publishing. The project’s engine is *Dot Dot Dot’s* successor *Bulletins of the Serving Library* – a journal that circulates as freely downloadable PDFs as well as a biannual print edition.\r\n\r\n(2015)',NULL),(328,1,'2016-04-29 00:45:13','2017-04-15 21:42:02',304,'RAFAL ZWIREK',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'rafal-zwirek',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nRafal Zwirek (b. 1970) holds a BA in Sociology from UAM in Poznań, Poland, and an MA from Andrzej Wajda Master School of Film Directing in Warsaw, Poland. \r\nHe has worked closely as a documentary filmmaker and cameraman with Artur Zmijewski, Pawel Althamer and other Polish artists on projects including exhibitions at the [7th Berlin Biennale](https://vimeo.com/167624889), the 51st and 55th Venice Biennale and the Museum of Modern Art, New York.\r\n',NULL),(329,1,'2016-04-29 01:09:55','2016-05-03 13:20:42',320,'BANK OF NO',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'bank-of-no',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(330,1,'2016-04-29 01:26:14','2016-05-03 13:21:06',325,'BANK OF NO / Leaflet',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'bank-of-no-leaflet',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(331,0,'2016-04-29 02:11:43','2016-04-29 02:30:14',310,'LABORATORY OF FRIENDS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'laboratory-of-friends',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(332,1,'2016-04-29 02:25:39','2017-04-19 07:15:19',313,'LABORATORY OF FRIENDS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'laboratory-of-friends',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nThis project is built on the principles of collaboration. Its basis is the *Theory Of Open Form*, with a concept related to visual arts. It was designed by Polish architect, artist and theorist Oskar Hansen.\r\n<br />\r\nAccording to the *Theory Of Open Form*, the artist with his/her gesture does not create a closed work of art, but builds an opportunity for the context and for interpretation. Open Form work is always ready to be present in other circumstances and conditions, in another time, and in another relationship with reality. It postulates classless society, egalitarianism, absence of hierarchical pattern, democracy, non-dogmatism, and decentralisation. Art in the convention of the Open Form respects the personality of the author and the personality of the viewer, and creates conditions and spaces for them to reflect. During the creation of work an ordinary human with his/her capabilities and skills can be the driving force.\r\n\r\nAccording to Hansen, the Open Form could be the ‘realism of our time’, and the role of the artist in it is to find the ‘personality’ and ‘identity’ of each and every person in order to prevent chaos. An emphasis is placed on everyone’s own creative individuality and sensitivity, since everyone is an author of the collective.\r\n',NULL),(333,0,'2016-05-03 10:29:58','2017-06-07 22:33:23',269,'VHS FESTIVAL: SPECIAL SCREENING',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'special-screening-vhs-festival',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\n17.09.2015, 20:00\r\n\r\nPress Release:\r\n\r\nThe first Cypriot VHS Festival will happen on 17 September 2015, with a special screening at Point Centre for Contemporary Art (free entrance). Selected, original trailers of the VHS movies that are part of the festival’s programme will be screened. \r\n\r\nTrailers, which both document how the videotape functioned as a self-advertising medium and show us what genres were popular at the time of their release, will appear either before and/or after the movie, or in the middle. \r\n\r\nFestival programme information, printed material and tickets will be available during the event.',NULL),(334,1,'2016-05-03 10:36:24','2017-06-07 22:33:00',270,'FIRST CYPRIOT VHS FESTIVAL ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'first-cypriot-vhs-festival',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\n<br />17.09.2015, 20:00\r\n\r\nPress Release I:\r\n\r\nThe first Cypriot VHS Festival will happen on 17 September 2015, with a special screening at Point Centre for Contemporary Art (free entrance). Selected, original trailers of the VHS movies that are part of the festival’s programme will be screened. \r\n\r\nTrailers, which both document how the videotape functioned as a self-advertising medium and show us what genres were popular at the time of their release, will appear either before and/or after the movie, or in the middle. \r\n\r\nFestival programme information, printed material and tickets will be available during the event.\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />23–27.09.2015\r\n\r\nPress Release II:\r\n\r\nFrom 23 to 27 September 2015, VHS CYPRUS will be hosting the [First Cypriot VHS Festival](https://vhscyprus.wordpress.com/) at Kosmiko Kentron Antonakis in Nicosia, where 10 Cypriot straight-to-video films by 10 different directors will be screened for the first time.\r\n\r\nDuring the festival there will also be Q&As with the films’ main casts and crews.\r\n\r\nVHS CYPRUS is an initiative led by artist Constantinos Taliotis that aims to unearth, preserve and disseminate Cypriot videocassette movies.\r\n\r\nFor more information email [vhscyprus@gmail.com](mailto:vhscyprus@gmail.com) or visit them at their Facebook page [VHS Cyprus](https://www.facebook.com/vhscyprus/).',NULL),(335,1,'2016-05-03 10:38:42','2017-06-07 22:35:11',272,'CONSTANTINOS TALIOTIS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'constantinos-taliotis',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\n[Constantinos Taliotis](http://www.constantinostaliotis.com/) (b. 1983, Cyprus) holds a BA in Fine Art from University of the Arts London and an MA from Middlesex University, UK. \r\n\r\nHe has had residencies at the ISCP, New York, 2014, and at Künstlerhaus Bethanien, Berlin, 2012. Solo shows of Taliotis include: *50 Years of James Bond against Architecture*, Pilot Galeri, Turkey, 2013; *Casting Modernist Architecture*, Künstlerhaus Bethanien, Germany, 2012; *You can be a cop, a criminal or a lawyer. When you are facing a loaded gun, what’s the difference?*, Apotheke,  Cyprus, 2011. In 2013, he co-represented the Republic of Cyprus at the 55th Venice Biennial.\r\n\r\n(2015)',NULL),(336,1,'2016-05-03 13:10:23','2016-05-03 13:17:36',307,'FAMAGUSTA GHOST TOWN',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'famagusta-ghost-town',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(337,1,'2016-05-03 13:34:48','2016-05-03 13:34:48',310,'LIVE ACT SCULPTING WORKSHOP',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'live-act-sculpting-workshop',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(338,1,'2016-05-03 13:40:17','2016-05-03 13:40:17',312,'NICOSIA AIRPORT ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'nicosia-airport',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(339,1,'2016-05-03 14:04:23','2016-05-03 14:04:23',315,'LIVE ACT SCULPTING - REACTOR SCULPTURE LAB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'live-act-sculpting-reactor-sculpture-lab',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(340,1,'2016-05-03 14:07:24','2016-05-03 14:07:24',317,'PHOTOGRAPHY WORKSHOP',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'photography-workshop',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(341,1,'2016-05-03 14:16:18','2017-04-19 16:39:11',327,'PICK NICK â€“ SILENT MARCH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pick-nick-silent-march',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(342,1,'2016-05-03 15:17:25','2017-05-30 23:06:43',75,'IOANNA MAKI',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'ioanna-maki',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nIoanna Maki holds a BA in History of Art from the University of Cambridge, St. Johns College and an MA in Museums and Galleries in Education from the Institute of Education, University of London. \r\n\r\nShe has worked as a museum educator for the Cyprus Educational Mission in the UK and has implemented a pilot educational programme for the A.G. Leventis Gallery of Cypriot Antiquities at the British Museum. She has also undertaken a research internship under Bettany Hughes, a London-based author, historian and BBC broadcaster.\r\n\r\n(2014)',NULL),(343,1,'2016-05-03 16:06:47','2017-06-01 23:28:30',189,'MARIA AND NEOPTOLEMOS MICHAELIDESâ€™S HOUSE',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'the-house',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(344,0,'2016-05-03 17:59:09','2016-09-14 12:30:26',9,'PROTARAS SEA RESORT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'protaras-sea-resort',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(345,1,'2016-05-05 16:25:57','2017-06-07 23:03:16',286,'018 SOMETHING QUEER',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'018-something-queer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(346,1,'2016-05-06 12:32:55','2017-05-25 16:38:04',300,'CHRISTINA LAMBROU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'christina-lambrou',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nChristina Lambrou (b. 1977, Cyprus) is a PhD candidate in History of Art at the Visual and Material Culture Research Centre / FADA, Kingston University, London. \r\n\r\nLambrou’s research examines the cultural production of Adamantios Diamantis (1900–1994) as an artist and an intellectual vis-à-vis the process of modernisation in Cypriot society and modernism in art. She also writes on visual arts for the cultural supplement of *Politis* daily newspaper and lectures in Art History at the University of Nicosia. She has contributed to multiple publications and talks, including International Museum Day at the State Gallery in Nicosia.\r\n\r\n(2013)',NULL),(347,1,'2016-05-06 13:22:58','2017-05-25 16:48:47',302,'THEODOULOS GREGORIOU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'theodoulos-gregoriou',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\n[Theodoulos Gregoriou](http://www.theodoulosgregoriou.com/) (b. 1956, Cyprus) studied Painting at the Institute de Arte Plastice N. Grigorescu in Bucharest, 1976–81, and worked at Cité International des Arts and at the École des Beaux Arts, Paris, 1986–87. \r\n\r\nGregoriou participated in the Venice Biennale (Aperto, 1990) and has exhibited his work at the National Museum, Warsaw, 1999; the Olympic Art Museum Seoul, South Korea; Museum Iancelevich La Luvier, Belgium; Kunsthaus Mannheim; Musée d’Art Modern, Osten, and Wattviller Apollonia, Strasburg, 2005. In 2008, he showed his work at the Louvre Museum. He divides his time between Nicosia and Paris.\r\n\r\n(2013)',NULL),(348,1,'2016-05-06 13:28:26','2017-05-25 16:56:34',303,'CHRISTOS HADJICHRISTOS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'christos-hadjichristos',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\n[Christos Hadjichristos](http://ucy.ac.cy/dir/en/component/comprofiler/userprofile/hristosh) (b. 1961, Cyprus) received his first degree in Architectural Engineering in 1986 from the University of Texas at Austin and a Master in Architecture in 1991 from the same institution. He was awarded a PhD in Architecture from Bartlett School of Graduate Studies at University College London in 2002. \r\n\r\nHe is currently an Associate Professor of [Architecture at the University of Cyprus](http://www.ucy.ac.cy/arch/en/). He taught at the American University of Beirut and at the Lebanese American University (2002–2003). He was one of the organisers and keynote speakers at the 31st Conference of IAPL (The International Association for Philosophy and Literature) *Layering: textual, visual, spatial, temporal*, which was hosted by the University of Cyprus in June 2007. He has received a number of awards in architectural competitions and he participated in the Venice Biennale for Cyprus in 2006 and 2008.\r\n\r\n(2013)',NULL),(349,1,'2016-05-06 13:35:30','2017-05-25 16:49:23',304,'MARINA YERALI',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'marina-yerali',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nMarina Yerali Christodoulou studied Book Arts (BA Hοns) at the London College of Communication and holds an MA in Book Arts with a specific focus on artists’ books from the University of the Arts in London.   \r\n\r\nShe was a research associate at the Visual Sociology and Museum Studies Lab of the Cyprus University of Technology and a librarian at Neapolis University Paphos. She has also worked as a picture research assistant in the Archives and Permissions Department of Thames and Hudson Ltd, where she archived special and rare photographic collections.\r\n\r\n(2013)',NULL),(350,1,'2016-05-06 13:39:15','2017-05-25 16:58:11',305,'ALKIS HADJIANDREOU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'alkis-hadjiandreou',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nAlkis Hadjiandreou (b. 1977, Cyprus) studied Architecture in Athens and Theatre Studies in Paris. He received the NRW Kultursekretariat Tanzrecherche #7, Nordrhein-Westfalen, 2011, and Open Call #2: Site specific installations, Nicosia Municipal Arts Centre, 2012. \r\n\r\nIn 2012, Hadjiandreou co-founded the art and research group [pick nick](http://www.picknickworks.org/) with Maria Petrides and Panayiotis Michael. He is a contributing author of *Placing Memory* (edited by Alexandra Chronaki and Petros Phokaides), *Christodoulos Panayiotou, Two Days After Forever*, and *The Swedish Dance History, vol. 4* (INPEX, Stockholm, 2013).\r\n\r\n(2013)\r\n',NULL),(351,1,'2016-05-06 13:42:35','2017-05-25 16:59:21',309,'POLYS PESLIKAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'polys-peslikas',NULL,NULL,'1970-01-01 01:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nPolys Peslikas (b. 1973, Cyprus) studied at the École des Beaux Arts in Montpellier, France. \r\n\r\nHe has presented solo exhibitions in Omikron Gallery, Nicosia, 2010; Archimede Staffolini Gallery, Nicosia, 1999, 2003 and 2005; Lab Art Projects, Athens, 2003, and Carré St Anne, Montpellier, 2002. He has taken part in a number of group shows, including exhibitions at Evagoras Lanitis Centre, Limassol, 2012; Phytorio, Nicosia, 2012; Omikron Gallery, Nicosia, 2011, and Nicosia Municipal Arts Centre, Nicosia, 2008.\r\n\r\n(2013)',NULL),(352,0,'2016-05-06 13:51:39','2016-05-16 09:49:49',306,'CHARA STEPHANOU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chara-stephanou',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bio \r\n\r\nChara Stephanou holds a BA Philosophy and Politics (University of Manchester, 2003) and an MA Aural and Visual Culture (Goldsmiths College, 2006). Between 2007 and 2010 she worked as a lecturer in higher education (University of Nicosia and University of Cyprus) and her MPhil research focused on the UN Buffer Zone in Cyprus. ',NULL),(353,1,'2016-05-06 13:51:39','2017-05-25 16:50:11',306,'CHARA STEPHANOU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chara-stephanou',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nChara Stephanou (b. 1983, Cyprus) holds a BA in Philosophy and Politics from the University of Manchester and an MA in Aural and Visual Culture from Goldsmiths College. \r\n\r\nBetween 2007 and 2010 she worked as a lecturer in higher education (University of Nicosia and University of Cyprus). Her MPhil research focused on the UN Buffer Zone in Cyprus. In 2011 she was a Research Fellow at the University of California, Berkeley.\r\n\r\n(2013)',NULL),(354,1,'2016-05-06 13:56:17','2017-10-16 15:39:15',308,'THEOPISTI STYLIANOU-LAMBERT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'theopisti-stylianou-lambert',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\n[Theopisti Stylianou-Lambert](https://cut.academia.edu/TheopistiStylianouLambert) earned her PhD in Museum Studies from the University of Leicester, UK. She holds an MA in Art Education from the Department of Visual Arts Studies at the University of Texas at Austin, USA, and an MA in Advertising from the College of Communications at the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign, USA.\r\n\r\nShe is an assistant professor in the Multimedia and Graphic Arts Department of the Cyprus University of Technology and the coordinator of the [Visual Sociology and Museum Studies Lab](https://vsmslab.com/). She has received several awards and scholarships including an Arts and Humanities Research Council Award, UK; an A. G. Leventis Foundation Scholarship, France; a Kelly Fearing Endowed Scholarship in Art Education and Studio Art, USA; an M. K. Hage Endowed Scholarship in Fine Arts, USA, and a Fulbright Scholarship, USA.\r\n\r\n(2013)',NULL),(355,0,'2016-05-06 14:00:26','2016-05-06 14:19:55',403,'GLORIA KASSIANIDES',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'gloria-kassianides',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bio\r\n\r\nGloria Kassianides is the founder and director of Gloria Galley, Cyprus\' longest established venue for contemporary arts. It has show-cased the work of well-known and up-coming artists for over 30 years, since the Gallery\'s foundation in 1977.',NULL),(356,0,'2016-05-06 14:00:59','2016-05-06 14:19:42',401,'GLORIA KASSIANIDES',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'356',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bio\r\n\r\nGloria Kassianides is the founder and director of Gloria Galley, Cyprus\' longest established venue for contemporary arts. She has show-cased the work of well-known and up-coming artists for over 30 years, since the Gallery\'s foundation in 1977.',NULL),(357,1,'2016-05-06 14:02:22','2017-04-13 22:17:04',401,'GLORIA KASSIANIDOU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'357',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nGloria Kassianidou (b. 1940, Greece) is the founder and director of [Gloria Gallery](http://www.gloriagallery.com/index.php?lang=en), Cyprus\' longest established venue for contemporary arts. She has been showcasing the work of well-known and up-and-coming artists for over 30 years, since the gallery\'s foundation in 1977.\r\n\r\n',NULL),(358,1,'2016-05-06 14:06:28','2017-05-25 17:00:15',400,'COSTAS MANTZALOS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'costas-mantzalos',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nProfessor [Costas Mantzalos](http://www.frederick.ac.cy/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=385&Itemid=593&lid=204) (b. 1963, Cyprus) was trained as a visual artist and also specialised in information design in the UK. He then completed a post-graduate degree at De Montfort University, UK, with a focus on post-modern graphic arts in Cyprus. \r\n\r\nHis first academic post at Frederick was in 1989. At present he is Dean of the School of Architecture, Fine and Applied Arts at Frederick. Parallel to his academic career, Mantzalos has been involved in numerous international art and design consultations. In 1996 he co-founded the art collective [TWO|FOUR|TWO](http://www.twofourtwo.com/) with architect Constantinos Kounnis.\r\n\r\n(2013)\r\n',NULL),(359,1,'2016-05-06 14:17:33','2017-05-25 17:03:03',402,'NATALIE HELLER',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'natalie-heller',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\n[Natalie Heller](http://www.natalieheller.com/) (b. 1983, Cyprus) holds a BA in Philosophy and French from Oxford University and an MA in Creative Practice from Trinity Laban in London. She also studied Dance at Dance New Amsterdam in NYC and Espedance in France. \r\n\r\nHer performance work has been supported by the Ministry of Culture and Education of Cyprus and the French Institute. Selected performance works include: *Eternal Recurrence*, 2013; *Still Here*, 2012; *Presence in Absence*, 2011, and *Moi Partant, Arthur Rimbaud*, 2010.\r\n\r\n(2013)',NULL),(360,0,'2016-05-06 14:23:15','2017-04-03 13:12:51',407,'ELENI LOIZIDOU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'eleni-loizidou',NULL,NULL,'1970-01-01 01:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nEleni Loizides (b. , ) living in Nicosia, is an Archaeological Conservator with a Bachelor from University College London and a Masters degree in Historic Building Conservation (MA University of York) and many years work experience in the field of archaeological and historic building conservation. \r\n<br/>\r\nSince 2008 she is working as a Conservator at the Department of Antiquities, Cyprus  Her main duties include the overall responsibility for the *Conservation Laboratory of Metallic and other Archaeological Artefacts* in Nicosia as well as the *Conservation Laboratory for Underwater Finds* in Larnaca. She has previously worked in London at English Heritage  and at War Memorials Trust (a non-profit organisation). In Cyprus she run her own private consultancy and conservation laboratory in Nicosia.',NULL),(361,1,'2016-05-06 14:32:00','2017-05-25 17:04:09',404,'RITA SEVERIS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'rita-severis',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br / >\r\nBio\r\n\r\nDr Rita C. Severis studied Philosophy at University College London and Journalism at the London School of Journalism. She earned her doctorate in Art History from Bristol University in England. \r\n\r\nShe is the author of the book *Travelling Artists in Cyprus: 1700–1960* (Philip Wilson Publishers, London) and the Founder and Executive Director of the [Centre of Visual Arts and Research (CVAR)](http://www.cvar.severis.org/en/) in Nicosia.\r\n\r\n(2013)',NULL),(362,1,'2016-05-06 14:56:41','2017-05-30 23:20:53',406,'GIORGOS PAPAGEORGIOU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'giorgos-papageorgiou',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nGiorgos Papageorgiou (b. 1970, Cyprus) served as Director of the Cyprus Theatre Organisation. He is the founder and director of The White Angel Company, a private theatre production company. He was involved in the Cyprus Cultural Foundation project and is currently a board member of the Rialto Theatre in Limassol.\r\n\r\n(2013)',NULL),(363,1,'2016-05-06 15:22:44','2017-04-19 07:02:27',408,'JOANNA LOUCA',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'joanna-louka',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\n[Joanna Louca](http://joannalouca.com/) (b. 1973, Cyprus) studied Woven Textiles at Middlesex University and obtained an MA in Textiles at Goldsmiths University, London. \r\n\r\nShe later worked as a freelancer and consultant in London. In 2001 she set up her company, Joanna Louca Designs Ltd, and launched her first main collection of hand-woven bags and scarves. Her atelier is based in Nicosia, Cyprus, where she designs and produces her hand-woven fabrics on domestic handlooms and works closely with Italian manufactures for the assembly of her accessories for her *Home* and *Fashion* collections.\r\n',NULL),(364,1,'2016-05-06 15:43:11','2017-10-18 11:59:49',450,'ANTONIS DANOS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'antonis-danos',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\n[Antonis Danos](http://cut.academia.edu/AntonisDanos) a BA in Philosophy from Southeast Missouri State University, a post-graduate diploma in History of Art and Architecture from the University of East Anglia, and an MA and PhD in History and Theory of Art, both from the University of Essex. \r\n\r\nBetween 2002 and 2007, Danos worked in higher education institutions in Cyprus. From 2007 on, he has been teaching and researching History and Theory of Art at the Cyprus University of Technology. He has published in journals including the *Journal of Modern Greek Studies*; *Nineteenth-Century Art Worldwide*, and *Kunapipi: Journal of Postcolonial Writing*, and wrote the two-volume book *Cypriot Artists: the Second Generation*, 2010. He also produced the documentary *Christoforos Savva: 1924–1968*, 2011, with film director Yannis Yapanis.\r\n\r\n(2013)',NULL),(365,1,'2016-05-06 15:48:30','2017-10-18 12:02:23',451,'KLITSA ANTONIOU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'klitsa-antoniou',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br/>\r\nBio\r\n\r\n[Klitsa Antoniou](http://frederick.academia.edu/KlitsaAntoniou) (b. 1968, Cyprus) graduated from Wimbledon School of Art, London, 1988, and Central St. Martins School of Art and Design, London, 1991. She holds an MA from the Pratt Institute, New York, 1993, and is currently a PhD candidate and Research Associate at Cyprus University of Technology. \r\n\r\nShe is Associate Professor in the Department of Art and Design at Frederick Institute of Technology and one of the founding members of the Artrageous Group. Exhibitions of her work have been held, among others, in the Hague, Thessaloniki, Quanzhou, Istanbul and Nicosia.\r\n\r\n(2013)',NULL),(366,1,'2016-05-06 15:54:29','2017-10-18 11:58:22',453,'NIKI LOUIZIDOU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'niki-louizidou',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nNiki Louizidou (b. Greece) studied Law at National and Kapodestrian University in Athens and History of Art at Ecole des Hautes Etudes et Sciences Sociales, VI Section in Paris, where she obtained her doctorate.\r\n\r\nShe is Emeritus Professor of History and Theory of Art in the Athens School of Fine Arts. She has taught courses related to history of art and visual culture at the University of Ioannina and Aristotle University, Thessaloniki; in the Department of History and Archaeology at the University of Crete and at the Athens School of Fine Arts in Athens, where she founded and headed the Department of Art History and Theory. Louizidou was a visiting professor at the University of Cyprus in 1995 and has had academic collaborations with universities in Amiens, Paris, Strasbourg and Essex.\r\n\r\n(2013)',NULL),(367,1,'2016-05-09 11:44:52','2017-05-25 17:02:19',412,'ELENI NIKITA',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'eleni-nikita',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nEleni Nikita (b. 1947, Cyprus) studied Social Sciences at the University of Geneva and received her PhD in Art History from the University of Athens. \r\n\r\nShe worked at the Social Research Centre (1971–1977) and then at the Cultural Services of the Cyprus Ministry of Education and Culture (1977–2009), where she served as director from 2003 to 2009. For many years she represented the Cyprus Ministry of Education and Culture on the Steering Committee for Culture, Heritage and Landscape and on various European Union committees. She was also the Secretary General of the Cyprus National Commission for UNESCO from 2001 to 2009. She is the author of numerous books and editions including *Adamantios Diamantis: His Life and Work*, 2000, and *Cyprus BV 97: Nicos Charalambides, Savvas Christodoulides, Lefteris Olympios, Theodoulos: La Biennale di Venezia, XLVII Esposizione internazionale d\'arte*, 1997.\r\n\r\n(2013)',NULL),(368,0,'2016-05-10 13:56:02','2017-03-14 15:44:21',420,'ALKIS HADJIANDREOU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'368',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nAlkis Hadjiandreou (b.1977, Cyprus) based in Nicosia and Paris, is an artist and architect. He studied architecture in Athens and theatre studies in Paris. \r\n\r\nHe has received the NRW Kultursekretariat Tanzrecherche #7, Nordrhein-Westfalen, 2011 and the Open Call #2: Site specific installations, Nicosia Municipal Arts Centre 2012. Invited by performer Myriam Lefkowitz, he was commissioned to produce work by Les Laboratoires d’Aubervilliers, Paris (2015). In 2012 Hadjiandreou co-founded art and research group, [pick nick](http://www.picknickworks.org/), with Maria Petrides and Panayiotis Michael. He is contributing author for *Placing Memory* (edited by Alexandra Chronaki and Petros Phokaides (Nissos Press, 2016); *Christodoulos Panayiotou, Two Days After Forever. A Reader on the Choreography of Time*, edited by Omar Kholeif (Sternberg Press, 2015); *The Swedish Dance History*, Vol. 4 (INPEX, Stockholm, 2013).',NULL),(369,1,'2016-05-11 14:16:45','2017-04-19 22:06:33',460,'VALENTINOS CHARALAMBOUS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'valentinos-haralambous',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nValentinos Charalambous (b. 1929, Cyprus) was born in Varosi to a family of traditional potters, and went on to study at Saint Martins in London. \r\n\r\nIn London he worked at the pottery studio of Bernard Leach. In 1957 he was asked by the Ministry of Education of Iraq to undertake the establishment of the Department of Ceramics at the Institute of Fine Arts in Baghdad. From 1967 until 1983 he served as the head of the department. After his retirement in 1983 he returned to Cyprus. In 1987 the Iraqi government honoured Charalambous for his contribution to the development of Iraqi art, both as a teacher and an artist. Charalambous still works with the Cultural Services of the Ministry of Education and Culture, where he is assigned to the development of Cyprus-Arab cultural relations.\r\n',NULL),(370,1,'2016-05-12 09:51:09','2017-05-25 16:58:44',454,'URSULA SAVVOPOULOU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'ursula-savvopoulou',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nUrsula Klara Tekeli-Savvopoulou (b. Poland) has been living in Cyprus since 1981. She graduated from the Department of Mediterranean Archaeology, Warsaw University, Poland and holds an MA and a PhD in Cypriology, with a specialisation in Ancient Cypriot Art. \r\n\r\nShe worked for the State Gallery of Contemporary Art of Cyprus for 22 years. Since 2001 she has been the president of the cultural group MALWA, founded by Poles who reside in Cyprus. She has received various honorary medals for her cultural activity by the Polish government and is a regular member of the London-based Polish Society of Art and Sciences Abroad.\r\n\r\n(2013)',NULL),(371,1,'2016-05-12 11:19:53','2017-04-13 22:40:29',458,'MARGARITA PARASKEVAIDOU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'margarita-paraskevaidou',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\n[Margarita Paraskevaidou](http://paraskevaidoumargarita.weebly.com/) (b. 1983, Nicosia) studied at the Academy of Fine Arts in Florence and obtained an MA in Arts Criticism from City University in London.\r\n\r\nSince 2007, she has been a regular columnist for *Phileleftheros* newspaper’s Sunday cultural section, and she is also a contributor for *Anef*, a quarterly cultural magazine. In September 2009 she was appointed by the Ministry of Culture and Education to the Advisory Committee for the Selection of Artworks for the State Gallery. During the past six years she has also been working as an art teacher, in both the private and public sectors.\r\n',NULL),(372,0,'2016-05-12 12:08:53','2016-10-18 23:21:42',463,'DEMETRIS TALIOTIS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'demetris-taliotis',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bio\r\n\r\n',NULL),(373,1,'2016-05-13 09:44:59','2017-04-17 15:14:24',468,'ARTEMIS ELEFTHERIADOU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'artemis-eleftheriadou',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nArtemis Eleftheriadou, holds a BA in Visual Communications and an MA in Art History from Goldsmiths University, UK. \r\n\r\nShe participated in the development of the BA programme in Graphic Design and Advertising and the MA programme in Interdisciplinary Design for the department of Applied Arts of Frederick University. She is currently an Associate Professor and Vice Dean of Frederick’s School of Architecture, Fine and Applied Arts, and teaches Graphic Design and Contemporary Art courses.\r\n\r\nShe was an invited member of the Cyprus Ministry of Education and Culture’s Advisory Committees for the Funding of Book Publications, 2004–07; Cypriot Publication Subsidies, 2004-2007, and Selection of Artworks for the State Gallery, 2006–09\r\n',NULL),(374,1,'2016-05-16 09:37:57','2017-05-25 16:47:55',469,'MARINA SCHIZA',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'marina-schiza',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nMarina Schiza (b. 1961, Cyprus) studied Art History at Richmond University, London. Since 1989 she has been working at the Phileleftheros Group, where she is editor-in-chief of the newspaper’s culture section. She has contributed to many publications, mainly with texts on 20th century Cypriot art. She is also the author of the books *Famagusta of the Artistic Creation*, 2008, and *Andreas Asproftas, Known and Unknown Works*, 2008. She has organised and curated a number of exhibitions, including *50 Years of Cypriot Artistic Creation*, 2010. She has also studied and published articles on the destruction of the cultural heritage in the occupied part of Cyprus and the illicit trade of Cypriot artworks abroad.\r\n\r\n(2013)',NULL),(375,1,'2016-05-16 10:06:12','2017-04-19 05:27:48',470,'ELENI LOIZIDOU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'375',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nEleni Loizidou (b. 1976, Nicosia) holds a BA in Conservation for Archaeology from University College London and an MA in Historic Building Conservation from the University of York. \r\n\r\nSince 2008 she has been working as a Conservator at the Department of Antiquities, Cyprus. Her main duties include overall management of the Conservation Laboratory of Metallic and other Archaeological Artefacts in Nicosia as well as the Conservation Laboratory for Underwater Finds in Larnaca. She has previously worked in London at English Heritage, where she was a government advisor on heritage matters, and at the War Memorials Trust, a non-profit organisation. In Cyprus she runs a private consultancy and conservation laboratory based in Nicosia.\r\n',NULL),(376,1,'2016-05-16 10:12:35','2017-05-25 16:55:55',471,'ANNA SOTERIADOU-NICOLAOU ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'anna-soteriadou-nicolaou',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nAnna Soteriadou-Nicolaou (b. 1965, Cyprus) is an entrepreneur mainly involved in property management and development. Anna has been an art lover and a collector all her life. Via the UNDO Foundation for Contemporary Art, which she co-founded with Andre Zivanari, she strives to honour excellence for deserving artists with talent, insight and commitment who aim to create beyond their country’s cultural boundaries. Together with her husband Polys, Anna has built a significant collection of contemporary art that includes work by international artists.\r\n\r\n(2013)',NULL),(377,1,'2016-05-19 14:30:49','2017-04-19 14:46:46',474,'MIKELLA PSARA',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'mikella-psara',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nMikella Psara (b. 1957, Cyprus) graduated from the Athens School of Fine Arts, Athens, 1981, where she studied under Demetris Mytaras, Yiorgos Mavroides and Yiannis Moralis. She also studied ceramics for two years. She has participated in the Bologna Biennale, 1988, and presented her work internationally in the former Yugoslavia, 1984, in Athens, 1987, and in Beijing, 1990.\r\n',NULL),(378,0,'2016-06-01 11:15:16','2017-02-22 15:51:06',800,'dfdf',N