ORILLAS FOUSKOPOLIS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'urban-gorillas',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(387,0,'2016-10-19 13:37:29','2016-10-19 13:41:46',83,'CHRISTODOULOS PANAYIOTOU ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'christodoulos-panayiotou',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'[Christodoulos](http://www.christodoulospanayiotou.com/news.php5) [Panayiotou](https://www.facebook.com/christodoulos.panayiotou.5/photos?source_ref=pb_friends_tl), (b. 1978, Cyprus) has studied performing arts at the Université Lumière Lyon and also holds a Masters in the same field from the University of Surrey and Université Lumière Lyon. He is an internationally acclaimed artist whose wide-ranging research focuses on the identification and uncovering of hidden narratives in the visual records of history and time.\r\n\r\nSolo exhibitions of his work have been held at: Centre d’Art Contemporain de Brétigny, France; [Museum of Contemporary Art, St. Louis](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Gq4UVOOAm0Q), USA; Museum of Contemporary Art, Leipzig, Germany; Kunsthalle Zürich, Switzerland; and Cubitt, London, UK. He has participated in major international survey exhibitions, including: the 8th Berlin Biennale; 7th Liverpool Biennial; Documenta 13, Kassel; 6th Taipei Biennale; Busan Biennale 2008. He was awarded The Future of Europe Prize in 2010, the DESTE Prize in 2005, and a [residency](http://www.bethanien.de/en/artists/christodoulos-panayiotou/) at Künstlerhaus Bethanien by [UNDO foundation](http://dev.o-r-g.com/point/annual-reports/2013/undo) in 2008.'),(388,0,'2016-10-19 13:38:45','2016-10-19 13:39:24',137,'CHRISTODOULOS PANAYIOTOU  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'388',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'[Christodoulos](http://www.christodoulospanayiotou.com/news.php5) [Panayiotou](https://www.facebook.com/christodoulos.panayiotou.5/photos?source_ref=pb_friends_tl), (b. 1978, Cyprus) has studied performing arts at the Université Lumière Lyon and also holds a Masters in the same field from the University of Surrey and Université Lumière Lyon. He is an internationally acclaimed artist whose wide-ranging research focuses on the identification and uncovering of hidden narratives in the visual records of history and time.\r\n\r\nSolo exhibitions of his work have been held at: Centre d’Art Contemporain de Brétigny, France; [Museum of Contemporary Art, St. Louis](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Gq4UVOOAm0Q), USA; Museum of Contemporary Art, Leipzig, Germany; Kunsthalle Zürich, Switzerland; and Cubitt, London, UK. He has participated in major international survey exhibitions, including: the 8th Berlin Biennale; 7th Liverpool Biennial; Documenta 13, Kassel; 6th Taipei Biennale; Busan Biennale 2008. He was awarded The Future of Europe Prize in 2010, the DESTE Prize in 2005, and a [residency](http://www.bethanien.de/en/artists/christodoulos-panayiotou/) at Künstlerhaus Bethanien by [UNDO foundation](http://dev.o-r-g.com/point/annual-reports/2013/undo) in 2008.'),(389,1,'2016-10-19 13:43:28','2017-05-25 15:37:09',138,'CHRISTODOULOS PANAYIOTOU ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'christodoulos-panayiotou',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\n[Christodoulos Panayiotou](http://www.christodoulospanayiotou.com/news.php5) (b. 1978, Cyprus) studied Performing Arts at Université Lumière Lyon and holds an MA in the same field from the University of Surrey and Université Lumière Lyon.\r\n\r\nSolo exhibitions of his work have been held at: Centre d’Art Contemporain de Brétigny, France; Museum of Contemporary Art, St. Louis, USA; Museum of Contemporary Art, Leipzig, Germany; Kunsthalle Zürich, Switzerland, and Cubitt, London, UK. He has participated in major international survey exhibitions, including: 7th Liverpool Biennial; Documenta 13, Kassel; 6th Taipei Biennale, and Busan Biennale 2008. He was awarded The Future of Europe Prize in 2010, the [DESTE Prize](http://deste.gr/deste-prize/deste-prize-2005/) in 2005, and a [residency](http://www.bethanien.de/en/artists/christodoulos-panayiotou/) at Künstlerhaus Bethanien by UNDO Foundation in 2008. He divides his time between Nicosia and Berlin.\r\n\r\n(2013)',NULL),(390,1,'2016-10-20 14:51:27','2017-10-13 12:38:58',NULL,'YIANNIS TOUMAZIS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'yiannis-toumazis',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio\r\n\r\nYiannis Toumazis (b. 1961, Cyprus) studied Civil Engineering at Metsovion National Polytechnic in Greece; Theatre Design at the Academy of Fine Arts in Utrecht, the Netherlands, and Theory of Art and Aesthetics at Université de Picardie Jules Verne in Amiens, France, where he received his PhD, presenting his thesis on Marcel Duchamp. \r\n\r\nSince 1994 he has been the Director of the Nicosia Municipal Arts Centre and of the [Pierides Foundation](http://www.pieridesfoundation.com.cy/main/default.aspx). He is also currently serving as Director of the Tornarites-Pierides Marine Life Foundation. He has designed, organised and curated a number of contemporary art exhibitions, including *Picasso-Graveur*; *Hommage a Van Gogh*; *Joan Miro*; *Accidental Meetings*, and *1960–1974: Young Cypriot Artists at the Dawn of the Republic*. In 2011, he was appointed the first Cypriot curator of the Cyprus Pavilion at the 54th Venice Biennale.\r\n\r\n(2013)',NULL),(391,1,'2016-10-20 16:06:29','2016-10-20 16:08:04',1,'A-Z',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'a-z',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Here is an alphabetical list of everything that has happened . . .',NULL),(392,0,'2016-10-20 16:06:37','2016-10-20 16:07:02',50,'A-Z',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'392',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(393,0,'2016-10-20 16:06:40','2016-10-20 16:07:13',50,'A-Z',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'393',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(394,0,'2016-10-20 16:39:27','2016-10-20 16:39:36',NULL,'test',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'test