nSince 1994, he is the Director of the Nicosia Municipal Arts Centre and of the [Pierides Foundation](http://www.pieridesfoundation.com.cy/main/default.aspx). He is also currently serving as Director of the Tornarites-Pierides Marine Life Foundation. He has designed, organised, and curated a number of contemporary art exhibitions, including Picasso-Graveur, Hommage a Van Gogh, Joan Miro, Accidental Meetings, 1960-1974 Young Cypriot Artists at the Dawn of the Republic etc. In 2011, he was appointed the first Cypriot curator of the Cyprus Pavilion at the 54th Venice.',NULL),(403,0,'2016-10-31 15:13:19','2016-10-31 15:13:51',NULL,'KONSTANTINA ZANOU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'konstantina-zanou',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio \r\n\r\nKonstantina Zanou (b. , ) living in New york, is a postdoctoral researcher at the Centre de Recherche en Histoire Européenne Comparé, Université Paris-Est Créteil. She received her Ph.D. from the Università di Pisa in 2007 and since then she has held research fellowships and teaching positions at the University of Nicosia, New York University, Centre for Advanced Studies Sofia Bulgaria, and Queen Mary University of London. \r\n\r\nShe is the co-editor (with Maurizio Isabella) of *Mediterranean Diasporas. Politics and Ideas in the Long Nineteenth Century* (Bloomsbury, forthcoming in July 2015) and the author of numerous articles on Greek expatriate intellectuals and national consciousness in the post-Venetian Adriatic, as well as on the spaces of the in-between in the Mediterranean. Her book in progress is tentatively titled *Stammering the Nation. Transnational Patriotism in the Mediterranean, 1800-1830*.\r\n',NULL),(404,0,'2016-10-31 15:14:11','2017-03-14 11:53:19',200,'KONSTANTINA ZANOU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'konstantina-zanou',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<br />\r\nBio \r\n\r\nKonstantina Zanou (b. , ) living in New york, is a postdoctoral researcher at the Centre de Recherche en